<subSubSection id="C30465748267131625F5834CFEBCFF48" lastPageId="69" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8267131725F5834CFC3CF886" blockId="68.[151,1436,1398,2034]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131725F5834CFE89F9FB" bold="true" box="[199,315,1615,1639]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C826713172752834CFD75F9FA" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[608,711,1615,1638]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED826713172752834CFD75F9FA" box="[608,711,1615,1638]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Arabian Peninsula. According to the distribution range of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131725878370FEAEF916" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[181,284,1651,1674]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131725878370FEAEF916" box="[181,284,1651,1674]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it occurs along the Northern strip of the Persian Gulf in 
<collectingCountry id="F309766F8267131726908370FC7DF916" box="[930,975,1651,1674]" name="Iran" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Iran</collectingCountry>
to the Makran Coast and central parts of 
<collectingCountry id="F309766F8267131725A58395FF44F932" box="[151,246,1686,1710]" name="Pakistan" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8267131724378395FEDAF932" box="[261,360,1686,1710]" captionStart="FIGURE 72" captionStartId="104.[151,250,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[213,1363,195,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-41@104.[212,1363,195,1942]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="FIGURE 72. Distribution range of (a) Eusparassus doriae group; (b) Eusparassus incertae sedis and Cercetius perezi. (a, b) with the same scale." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 72b</figureCitation>
). However, it was not surprising to encounter this species on the Southern shores of the Persian Gulf. This single male specimen has all the diagnostic character of this species. In addition to the characters of copulatory structure, it has the diagnostic vase-like dark marking on the opisthosoma ventrally (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8267131721CA83DDFAECF96A" box="[1272,1374,1758,1782]" captionStart="FIGURE 56" captionStartId="88.[151,250,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-74@88.[151,1436,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="FIGURE 56. Habitus and ventral views of Eusparassus spp. (a) Eusparassus educatus spec. nov. paratype male from Namibia; (b) Eusparassus tuckeri (Lawrence, 1927) comb. nov., female from Namibia; (c–d) Eusparassus xerxes (Pocock, 1901) (c syntype male from Pakistan, d syntype subadult male from Iran); (e–f) Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, female from Ladakh, Himalayas, India." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 56d</figureCitation>
). For detailed species description, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B0E8267131727368201FC38F886" author="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P." box="[516,906,1794,1819]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="2439 - 2496" refId="ref51693" refString="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P. (2012 a) Taxonomic revision of the huntsman spider genus Eusparassus Simon, 1903 (Araneae: Sparassidae) in Eurasia. Journal of Natural History, 46, 39 - 40, 2439 - 2496." type="journal article" year="2012">Moradmand and Jäger (2012a: 43)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8267131725F58225FCE8F86E" blockId="68.[151,1436,1398,2034]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131725F58225FE07F8A3" bold="true" box="[199,437,1830,1855]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Systematic position.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C82671317248E8224FD25F8A2" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[444,663,1831,1854]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED82671317248E8224FD25F8A2" box="[444,663,1831,1854]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131726618225FC17F8A2" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1932" box="[851,933,1830,1854]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dufouri">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131726618225FC17F8A2" box="[851,933,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">dufouri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131726EE8224FBFEF8A2" authorityName="Moradmand" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[988,1100,1831,1854]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestigator">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131726EE8224FBFEF8A2" box="[988,1100,1831,1854]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">vestigator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups due to the presence of the dark marking on the ventral opisthosoma, but the females differ in having not fused AMLL of epigyne. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C82671317243E826DFEE7F81A" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[268,341,1902,1926]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED82671317243E826DFEE7F81A" box="[268,341,1902,1926]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the latter character. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C826713172795826CFC37F81A" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[679,901,1903,1926]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED826713172795826CFC37F81A" box="[679,901,1903,1926]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has four thick bristles, a character shared with the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131725F18290FE81F836" authorityName="Moradmand" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[195,307,1939,1962]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestigator">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131725F18290FE81F836" box="[195,307,1939,1962]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">vestigator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but it differs in lacking the autapomorphic character of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131721748290FB04F836" authorityName="Moradmand" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1094,1206,1939,1962]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestigator">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131721748290FB04F836" box="[1094,1206,1939,1962]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">vestigator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, the strongly developed vRTA. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C82671317273782B4FDDEF852" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[517,620,1975,1998]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED82671317273782B4FDDEF852" box="[517,620,1975,1998]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could not be placed in any of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131726D682B4FBE1F852" authorityName="Moradmand" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[996,1107,1975,1998]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestigator">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131726D682B4FBE1F852" box="[996,1107,1975,1998]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">vestigator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C82671317215282B5FB1BF852" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1120,1193,1974,1998]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED82671317215282B5FB1BF852" box="[1120,1193,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131721FF82B5FA92F852" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1932" box="[1229,1312,1974,1998]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dufouri">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131721FF82B5FA92F852" box="[1229,1312,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">dufouri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups. Its geographical distribution also supports this intermediate status.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8266131625F5859BFA2EFF33" blockId="69.[151,1436,151,212]" box="[199,1436,151,176]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8266131625F5859BFDECFF2C" bold="true" box="[199,606,151,176]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Known geographical distribution.</emphasis>
